                  </persName>
            . I was on duty in Newgate-street on the 5th of May; the prosecutor came and gave the prisoner into my charge.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-251-person1357">
                  NATHANIEL 
                  ROUTH
               <interp inst="t18280529-251-person1357" type="surname" value="ROUTH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-251-person1357" type="given" value="NATHANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-251-person1357" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was at Guildhall when the prisoner was brought there; he was discharged, to be sent on board a ship - as I went along with him, I said, "It is a pity the man should lose his property;" he then cried, and said, he would show me where it was - he took me to the pawnbroker's; and said, he did not intend to go away without letting the man know where it was.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-251-person1358">
                  HENRY 
                  WHARTON
               <interp inst="t18280529-251-person1358" type="surname" value="WHARTON"></interp>
